  "prompt": "How many credits must you take for 2nd semester in VIT?",
  "response": "In VIT (Vellore Institute of Technology), the number of credits a student must take typically depends on their specific program and year of study. Generally, VIT follows a credit system based on the choice-based credit system (CBCS), and students are usually required to take around 20-24 credits per semester.\n\nFor the 2nd semester, students usually follow the curriculum set for their specific program which might include core courses, elective courses, practical labs, and project work. It's always best to consult the academic manual provided by VIT or your academic advisor to get precise information on the number of credits needed for your particular program and semester.\n\nIf you need detailed information regarding your specific course or semester, you should check the official VIT handbook or academic guidelines or reach out directly to your academic coordinator.",
